author: Odeinoichus
title: Crominus and his Speedor
review:
Set #70103 Boulder Bowling: I'm afraid that this is one of the weaker offerings from the Speedorz range, mind you the Mini-Figure is a must own and this is the cheapest method of obtaining him, however unless you're really into the Game the price and the piece count really do not help in making this worth purchasing.

First off there is really nothing to build here, the 'model' that is used as part of the game is a very flimsy looking build, mostly because it is designed to fall apart when struck by a Speedor. Hence the term Boulder Bowling for the name of this set, I suppose if you want the LEGO Boulder piece this is a great parts pack for that, unfortunately as a 'model' it isn't worth much.

The Speedor is an interesting piece, I neglected to mention in the Skunk Attack review that these replacements for the Spinners have just as much detail work put into the design and printing of them. Crominus has a sinister looking lime green and grey Speedor with side printing that captures the look of the Mini-Figures face pretty decently. Unlike Skinnet's Speedor, Crominus' has a few pieces extra that help to balance it when on display, so if you aren't playing the game, but like the Speedor design as a battle chariot for Mini-Figures this one looks great on a shelf. A few more Speedors and I think I'll like them just as well as the Spinners from Ninjago.

Crominus is the leader of the Crocodile Tribe, and his Mini-Figure is found in only two sets aside from this one, I believe he's in both Cragger's Command Ship and the newer Croc Swamp Hideout. This is the cheapest way to get him and he's well worth owning. His dual-sided torso and leg printing help make him stand out as a true leader, most of all the armor is designed to accomodate his red ragged looking cape which just looks... Brilliant.

His headpiece is pretty much the same as all the other Crocodiles, except of course where the printing is concerned, he's wearing a golden helmet and has gold teeth, his double-sided head has a great looking print for a Mini-Figure, definitely stands out. An interesting note is he does not appear to feature the same Powered up by CHI expression that most of the others get, with the wide eyes and such. Instead his expressions are both regal looking, one side appears more sinister than the other with a wider smile and slanted eyes.

Acessories include the typical mace weapon we've seen many times before. Not much to it really, but his personal weapon is much nicer, made out of all gold plastic abs it is basically a lightsaber hilt with a brand new serrated edged sword piece. Also attached to the hilt is a red jewel, perhaps a power source, not too sure, and a red lightsaber bar. The weapons of the Chima Mini-Figures must run on some kind of CHI Energy, however I haven't seen every episode so I'm not sure why they've got red energy in their weapons as there are no red CHI Energy crystals.

The five cards for the game in this set are: Crominus' character card, Chompor V12, Grandiorus (Perhaps the name of his signature weapon), Krank (Apparently the name of the mace he wields) and Shredant. LEGO's cards are pretty fun looking honestly and a big part of the reason why I collect Speedorz aside from the Mini-Figures.

Overall I think this is an ok set for fans of the Chima Mini-Figures and who aren't sure of getting Crominus' larger more expensive sets. But as far as part of the Speedorz game goes, this one is a bit weaker compared to Skunk Attack's play feature. It's a good parts pack for LEGO boulders if you're looking for some to include in your MOCs, still I'd recommend trying to get this on sale in Canada as it is certainly not worth 20$ before taxes.

author: RandOpossum
title: Crominus speedorz
review: I find this set pretty mediocre. I don't think 15 bucks is really worth it for such a simple build, so I put my value for money in 2. I like building, so the experience is a 4. I didn't take too long to build it, but it was a nice pastime. The object that stole the spotlight for me was Crominus himself and his speedorz. Great design as always. 15 bucks is not worth it, but it's great if you're collecting speedorz or minifigs. :)
